 <title>Manage Nexus public repositories</title>
 <para>As seen before, the "Anonymous" user can have read permission on a repository, to allow anyone to access and download artifact from this repository.</para>
  <sect2>
 <para>In order to set an anonymous access to your repository, you'll have to check : </para>
   <itemizedlist>
   <listitem>
      <para><emphasis>"Anonymous" user is activated by default, without any permission</emphasis></para>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
      <para><emphasis>When you create a "release" type repository "repositoryname", a role named "repositoryname-anonymous" has to be created, with access and download rigths on "repositoryname".</emphasis></para>
   </listitem>
   </itemizedlist>
   <para>Then as forge administrator, you'll have to add a role "repositoryname-anonymous" to "Anonymous" user to allow anyone to access and download artifacts on this repository :</para>
  <figure>
    <title>Add role "projet1_nexus_release (Anonymous)" </title>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata align="center" fileref="nexus_add_anonymous_role.png"/>
      </imageobject>
    </mediaobject>
  </figure>
</sect2>
